President Trump has designated certain funding as emergency requirements in accordance with the Department of Defense and Labor, Health and Human Services, and Education Appropriations Act, 2019 and Continuing Appropriations Act, 2019. This designation is in line with section 251(b)(2)(A) of the Balanced Budget and Emergency Deficit Control Act of 1985. The specific accounts referenced in section 7058(d) of Public Law 115-141 are included in this designation. The details of this action can be found in the enclosed memorandum from the Director of the Office of Management and Budget.